Cheers ! There are no PEP8 issues in this Pull Request. :beers: 

##### Comment last updated on August 14, 2017 at 20:23 Hours UTC
My first instinct would be to `raise` on PyPy with `deep=True` rather than stubbing a value, but don't feel strongly about it.
not a big fan of downstream having to deal with this. I suppose using the default argument is ok.
